data.text:
(2016)

• Missed the season due to injury

(2015)

• Redshirted due to injury

AS A SOPHOMORE (2014)

• Played in all 16 games, registering 27 points on 21 assists and six goals

• Notched nine ground balls, six draws and five caused turnovers

• Registered five assists vs. Detroit and scored twice against Saint Mary's

AS A FRESHMAN (2013)

• Played in 15 games, starting one of them

• Notched goals against Saint Mary's and Stetson

• Also collected six ground balls, two draws and caused five turnovers

HIGH SCHOOL/CLUB SUCCESS

• Competed for the Ultimate Goal Lacrosse Club, where she boasted 226 career goals

• Named offensive MVP in 2011 and 2012, earned all-league honors from 2009-12 and was the team captain in 2011 and 2012

• A member of the U.S. Lacrosse National Tournament Team for Pennsylvania in 2010 and 2011

• Also an Academic All-American in 2011 and 2012

• Other academic honors include Distinguished Honor Roll, Principal's Top 10 Percent, National Honor Society, Student Council and the Future Business Leaders of America

• Played field hockey in 2011 and 2012

PERSONAL

• Integrative biology major, intends on becoming a surgeon

• Will attend Harvard Medical School in the fall of 2016

• Parents are Douglas and Jacquie Beck

• Has two brothers, Brian and Kyle

• Born on Dec. 21, 1993, in Pennsylvania
